SUMMER ASSIGNMENT

SUMMER ASSIGNMENT click here

OFFICER INTERVIEWS:

If you plan to interview for an officer position, please make sure your name is on this list. We will be in touch soon with an interview time.

OFFICER INTERVIEW LIST

INTERVIEWS will be TUESDAY, June 24 from 11am - 1pm. Come any time during those hours. Please bring some new ideas you may have for next year! We will have pizza (because I'm Italian) and cake (because it's Emily's bday). If you can stay a little while, we will also be compiling the mailing for our summer assignment.

Auditions for 2019-2020 Choirs

Auditions for next year's choirs are in TWO parts: A Sextet or Octet live performance (grading rubric below) and a recording of you singing your part for "O Holy Night" (sheet music and learning tracks below) as part of the Disney Candlelight Processional.

Students who are NOT currently in an ensemble:

See Mr. Shafer personally AND:

Prepare YOUR voice part for "O Holy Night" from m. 1 through m. 14.

See sheet music and learning tracks below.

Current 8th GRADE CHORUS members:

Auditions will be dates TBA

1. Sing "Can You Hear" (Popouli) in a Sextet (S, S, A, A, B, B). letter F through the End.

2. Prepare YOUR voice part for "O Holy Night" from m. 1 through m. 14.

See sheet music and learning tracks below.

Current FESTIVAL CHORUS members:

Auditions will be Friday, 3/22-Friday, 3/29

1. Sing "Whose Garden Was This" (Regelski) in a Sextet (S, S, A, A, B, B). m.39 through m. 61

2. Prepare YOUR voice part for "O Holy Night" from m. 1 through m. 14.

See sheet music and learning tracks below.

Current TREBLE CHOIR members:

Auditions will be Friday, 3/29 - Friday, 4/5

1. Sing "Frobisher Bay" in a Sextet (S, S, M, M, A, A). m. 85 through the end of the piece.

2. Prepare YOUR voice part for "O Holy Night" from m. 1 through m. 14.

See sheet music and learning tracks below.

Current CONCERT CHOIR members:

Auditions will be Friday, 3/29 - Friday, 4/5

1. Sing "Alleluia" (Thompson) in an Octet (S, S, A, A, T, T, B, B) m. 1 through the top of pg. 5

2. Prepare YOUR voice part for "O Holy Night" from m. 1 through m. 14.

See sheet music and learning tracks below.
